            <p class="astro-privacy-policy">Many web browsers, along with certain mobile operating systems and apps, offer a Do-Not-Track ('DNT') option, allowing users to express their preference against having their online browsing behavior monitored or collected. Currently, there is no universally accepted standard for how DNT requests are interpreted and acted upon. Consequently, our Service does not presently acknowledge or react to DNT signals or similar mechanisms conveying your choice to opt-out of online tracking. Should future regulations necessitate compliance with a specific standard for online tracking, we will duly update our practices and notify you through an amended privacy policy.</p>
